"title": "1653: numbers, 6–10",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1653: numbers, 6-10",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The number seven is especially associated with completeness and perfection.  The number ten is occasionally used as a symbol of completeness.  Other numbers have a variety of associations.</p>\n<h2>Six</h2>\n<h3>The world was created in six days</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:11\">EXO 20:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:1-Gen1:31\">GEN 1:1–1:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:17\">EXO 31:17</a></p>\n<h3>Human work is to be limited to six days a week</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:26\">EXO 16:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:9\">EXO 20:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:13\">DEU 5:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:12\">EXO 23:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:15\">EXO 31:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:21\">EXO 34:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:2\">EXO 35:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:3\">LEV 23:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:14\">LUK 13:14</a></p>\n<h3>Other important six-day periods</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:8\">DEU 16:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:3-Josh6:14\">JOS 6:3–6:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:1\">MAT 17:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:2\">MRK 9:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:1\">JHN 12:1</a></p>\n<h3>Human work restricted to six-year periods</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:2\">EXO 21:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:10\">EXO 23:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:3\">LEV 25:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:12\">DEU 15:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:18\">DEU 15:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:14\">JER 34:14</a></p>\n<h2>Seven</h2>\n<h3>The seventh day is a day of rest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:2-Gen2:3\">GEN 2:2–2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:10\">EXO 20:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:14\">DEU 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:15-Exod31:17\">EXO 31:15–31:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:2-Exod35:3\">EXO 35:2–35:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:4\">HEB 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>The seventh year symbolises rest and freedom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:4\">LEV 25:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:10-Exod23:11\">EXO 23:10–23:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:2-Lev25:6\">LEV 25:2–25:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:1\">DEU 15:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:12\">DEU 15:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:31\">NEH 10:31</a></p>\n<h3>Major festivals lasted seven days</h3>\n<p>Unleavened Bread:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:15\">EXO 12:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:15\">EXO 23:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:6\">LEV 23:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:17\">NUM 28:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:8\">DEU 16:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:21\">2CH 30:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:17\">2CH 35:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:21\">EZK 45:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:34\">LEV 23:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:12\">NUM 29:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:13\">DEU 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:30\">EXO 29:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:35\">EXO 29:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:33\">LEV 8:33</a></p>\n<h3>The Feast of Weeks, or Pentecost, comes seven weeks after the firstfruits of the harvest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:15-Lev23:16\">LEV 23:15–23:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:9\">DEU 16:9</a></p>\n<h3>Festivals in the seventh month</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:29\">LEV 16:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:24\">LEV 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:39\">LEV 23:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:7\">NUM 29:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:12\">NUM 29:12</a></p>\n<h3>Important rituals associated with sevens</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:6-Lev4:17\">LEV 4:6–4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:7\">LEV 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:51\">LEV 14:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:14\">LEV 16:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:11\">NUM 28:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:26\">1CH 15:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:8\">JOB 42:8</a></p>\n<h3>Ritual uncleanness for seven days</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:2\">LEV 12:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:4\">LEV 13:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:21\">LEV 13:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:26\">LEV 13:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:24\">LEV 15:24</a></p>\n<h3>Seven times indicates a completed action</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:18\">LEV 26:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:4\">JOS 6:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:43\">1KI 18:43</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:10\">2KI 5:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:164\">PSA 119:164</a></p>\n<h3>Seven times indicates total intensification</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:15\">GEN 4:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:21\">LEV 26:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps12:6\">PSA 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:12\">PSA 79:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:26\">ISA 30:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:19\">DAN 3:19</a></p>\n<h3>The seven spirits of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:6\">REV 5:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:10\">ZEC 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:4\">REV 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:1\">REV 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:5\">REV 4:5</a></p>\n<h3>Seven associated with final judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:9\">REV 21:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:2\">REV 8:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:6\">REV 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev10:3-Rev10:4\">REV 10:3–10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:3\">REV 12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:1\">REV 15:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:7\">REV 15:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:3\">REV 17:3</a></p>\n<h2>Eight</h2>\n<h3>Eighth day as the day of circumcision</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:21\">LUK 2:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:12\">GEN 17:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:4\">GEN 21:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:3\">LEV 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:59\">LUK 1:59</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:8\">ACT 7:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:5\">PHP 3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Eighth day as the end of major festivals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:36\">LEV 23:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:39\">LEV 23:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:35\">NUM 29:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:9\">2CH 7:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:18\">NEH 8:18</a></p>\n<h3>Rituals of the eighth day</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:10\">LEV 14:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:23\">LEV 14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:14\">LEV 15:14</a></p>\n<h2>Nine</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ died at the ninth hour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:45-Matt27:46\">MAT 27:45–27:46</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:33-Mark15:34\">MRK 15:33–15:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:44\">LUK 23:44</a></p>\n<h2>Ten</h2>\n<h3>Ten as a symbol of completeness</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:2\">RUT 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:6-2Chr4:8\">2CH 4:6–4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:12-Dan1:15\">DAN 1:12–1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:24\">DAN 7:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:3\">REV 12:3</a></p>\n<h3>Ten as an approximate number</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:7\">GEN 31:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:4\">RUT 1:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:8\">1SA 1:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:3\">JOB 19:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:23\">ZEC 8:23</a></p>\n<h3>Ten days as an approximate period</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:55\">GEN 24:55</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:38\">1SA 25:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:6\">ACT 25:6</a></p>\n<h3>Ten plagues on Egypt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:20\">EXO 7:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:6\">EXO 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:16\">EXO 8:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:24\">EXO 8:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:6\">EXO 9:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:10\">EXO 9:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:22\">EXO 9:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:12\">EXO 10:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:21\">EXO 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod11:5\">EXO 11:5</a></p>\n<h3>The Ten Commandments</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:28\">EXO 34:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:13\">DEU 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:4\">DEU 10:4</a></p>\n<h3>Tens in Jesus Christ's parables</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:1\">MAT 25:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:28\">MAT 25:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:8\">LUK 15:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:13\">LUK 19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:17\">LUK 19:17</a></p>",
